17: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775857024887,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ad6f16ffesjUNLGKzJUQsJL\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7952da2e001bpexF7Jo9cWCnK\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7952ca60001caLMkZvwAP4uYs\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ad6f16ffesjUNLGKzJUQsJL\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_c29755b8d3f54de3a8d567dc\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md\",\"content\":\"# Proposal: Valkey Storage Implementation (AR-014)\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nImplement the Valkey backend for the session storage interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage with indexed queries for garbage collection based on expiry and last-activity timestamps.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe Valkey storage implementation provides an alternative backend for session persistence in the agentcube project. It enables:\\n\\n1. **Session persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox information using Valkey key-value storage\\n2. **Garbage collection support**: Maintain sorted set indices for expiry and last-activity based cleanup\\n3. **Deployment flexibility**: Valkey offers Apache 2.0 licensing and enhanced performance characteristics\\n4. **Atomic operations**: Use Valkey `DoMulti` to ensure consistent index updates\\n5. **Cluster awareness**: Support for comma-separated addresses and cluster-specific options\\n\\nThis implementation is the focus of AR-014 and builds upon the interface defined in AR-012, running in parallel with the Redis implementation from AR-013.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\n### In Scope\\n\\n- `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Valkey implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\\n- `sessionKey()` helper function for consistent key construction (shared with Redis)\\n- `makeValkeyOptions()` for environment variable parsing and client configuration\\n- All `Store` interface methods implemented with Valkey fluent API\\n- `DoMulti` operations for atomic multi-command operations\\...\n  Line 20: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775857030874,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ad6f16ffesjUNLGKzJUQsJL\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7953d2a6001HfRoSysPhpM62U\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7953bf9d001UNoLBcQIqYZVkV\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ad6f16ffesjUNLGKzJUQsJL\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Done. Created `changes/AR-014/proposal.md` for the Valkey storage implementation following the same structure as AR-013 (Redis), with Valkey-specific details including:\\n\\n- `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client library\\n- `DoMulti` for atomic operations\\n- `IsValkeyNil` for nil detection\\n- MGET optimization with cluster slot considerations\\n- Optional flags: `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE`\\n- Comma-separated address support for cluster deployments\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775857030873,\"end\":1775857030873}}}\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-017_ST-2.log:\n  Line 27: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775856939451,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ae3044ffemHzEQmhqlh3J9m\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d795270bd001CKbFx3Mj9zuF0l\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d795257d4001Bdzl22aY9nI3yx\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ae3044ffemHzEQmhqlh3J9m\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"toolu_d63458f576f24407ba8cb555\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"**/changes/**/*\"},\"output\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/be