{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857608269,"sessionID":"ses_286a40e50ffeZrmUJfaiddgD48","part":{"id":"prt_d795ca61b001pBk108Staeu5wv","messageID":"msg_d795c9acf001Cem7uFG8ann6QN","sessionID":"ses_286a40e50ffeZrmUJfaiddgD48","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_tool-7df9bd8265df43268396fab69d3af346","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"tail -100 /home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-014_ST-7.log 2>/dev/null | grep -A 50 \"AR-014\"","description":"Read AR-014 summary from log"},"output":"{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775852484381,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e751d001S6jiX8pNvbjXwr\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e6854001Dm1vYsVM9oRy2e\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I'll search for the AR-014 archive record and related Valkey storage implementation documentation.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775852484379,\"end\":1775852484379}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775852485407,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e771e001j3Z739DQD4J7iy\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e6854001Dm1vYsVM9oRy2e\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"toolu_5d6b7bac41da4997abd14a38\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"AR-014\"},\"output\":\"Found 6 matches\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md:\\n  Line 1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Tasks\\n  Line 94: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md` (if exists)\\n\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/design.md:\\n  Line 7: | AR | AR-014 |\\n\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\\n  Line 3: AR: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\\n\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md:\\n  Line 1: # Delta Spec: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\\n\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md:\\n  Line 1: # Proposal: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\",\"metadata\":{\"matches\":6,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"AR-014\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775852485395,\"end\":1775852485406}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775852485421,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e7922001qtHYgOT9KmoG78\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e6854001Dm1vYsVM9oRy2e\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"toolu_20a8fd993a704a278234f4b9\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"**/agentcube/**/*AR*\"},\"output\":\"No files found\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":0,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775852485401,\"end\":1775852485416}}}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1775852485444,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e7b2c001iaO0XkY9KbI1k8\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e6854001Dm1vYsVM9oRy2e\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":15046,\"input\":41,\"output\":152,\"reasoning\":0,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":14853}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1775852486713,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e8035001x49srpI6pXAgO2\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e7b65001LGdvM8uiVZ64Sv\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"snapshot\":\"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775852489687,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e82d9001yC19Vtk15ARmX2\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e7b65001LGdvM8uiVZ64Sv\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_b07a9015917946c1950fd64e\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\\n2: \\n3: ## Module\\n4: `pkg/store`\\n5: \\n6: ## Language\\n7: Go\\n8: \\n9: ## Size\\n10: S\\n11: \\n12: ---\\n13: \\n14: ## Requirement: Valkey provider selection\\n15: \\n16: The system SHALL support Valkey as a store backend when `STORE_TYPE` is set to `valkey` (case-insensitive).\\n17: \\n18: ### Scenario: Valkey provider selected\\n19: \\n20: - **GIVEN** environment variable `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\\n21: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is first called\\n22: - **THEN** the Valkey implementation is initialized\\n23: \\n24: ---\\n25: \\n26: ## Requirement: Valkey client initialization\\n27: \\n28: The system SHALL create a Valkey client using `valkey-go` library with address and password from environment variables.\\n29: \\n30: ### Scenario: Valkey client created with multiple addresses\\n31: \\n32: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=valkey-node-1:6379,valkey-node-2:6379` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD=secret`\\n33: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\\n34: - **THEN** client is created with `InitAddress: [\\\"valkey-node-1:6379\\\", \\\"valkey-node-2:6379\\\"]` and `Password: \\\"secret\\\"`\\n35: \\n36: ### Scenario: Valkey client with cache disabled\\n37: \\n38: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` and valid `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\\n39: - **WHEN** Valkey options are built\\n40: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is set to `true` on the client options\\n41: \\n42: ### Scenario: Valkey client with single client mode\\n43: \\n44: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true` and valid `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\\n45: - **WHEN** Valkey options are built\\n46: - **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is set to `true` on the client options\\n47: \\n48: ---\\n49: \\n50: ## Requirement: Valkey Ping operation\\n51: \\n52: The system SHALL verify Valkey connectivity by sending PING command and expecting \\\"PONG\\\" response.\\n53: \\n54: ### Scenario: Ping successful\\n55: \\n56: - **GIVEN** a running Valkey server\\n57: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Valkey store\\n58: - **THEN** command `B().Ping()` returns string \\\"PONG\\\"\\n59: \\n60: ### Scenario: Ping fails on disconnected server\\n61: \\n62: - **GIVEN** Valkey server is unavailable\\n63: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\\n64: - **THEN** error is returned indicating connection failure\\n65: \\n66: ---\\n67: \\n68: ## Requirement: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID\\n69: \\n70: The system SHALL retrieve sandbox JSON by session key using GET command.\\n71: \\n72: ### Scenario: Session found\\n73: \\n74: - **GIVEN** key `session:test-session` exists with valid JSON in Valkey\\n75: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \\\"test-session\\\")` is called\\n76: - **THEN** returns `*types.SandboxInfo` with data unmarshaled from JSON\\n77: \\n78: ### Scenario: Session not found\\n79: \\n80: - **GIVEN** key `session:missing-session` does not exist in Valkey\\n81: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \\\"missing-session\\\")` is called\\n82: - **THEN** returns `ErrNotFound` (detected via `IsValkeyNil`)\\n83: \\n84: ---\\n85: \\n86: ## Requirement: Valkey StoreSandbox\\n87: \\n88: The system SHALL store sandbox JSON using SETNX and update both ZSET indexes in one DoMulti batch.\\n89: \\n90: ### Scenario: Store new sandbox\\n91: \\n92: - **GIVEN** a valid `*types.SandboxInfo` with `SessionID=newsession` and `ExpiresAt` set\\n93: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\\n94: - **THEN** executes DoMulti with: SETNX `session:newsession`, ZADD to `session:expiry`, ZADD to `session:last_activity`\\n95: \\n96: ### Scenario: Store sandbox with zero ExpiresAt\\n97: \\n98: - **GIVEN** `*types.SandboxInfo` with `ExpiresAt` set to zero time\\n99: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\\n100: - **THEN** error indicates invalid expiration time\\n101: \\n102: ### Scenario: Store nil sandbox\\n103: \\n104: - **GIVEN** nil sandbox pointer\\n105: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\\n106: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\\n107: \\n108: ---\\n109: \\n110: ## Requirement: Valkey UpdateSandbox\\n111: \\n112: The system SHALL update existing sandbox JSON using SET with XX flag.\\n113: \\n114: ### Scenario: Update existing sandbox\\n115: \\n116: - **GIVEN** key `session:existing` exists with valid JSON\\n117: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, updatedSandbox)` is called\\n118: - **THEN** executes SET with XX flag, expects response `ToString() == \\\"OK\\\"`\\n119: \\n120: ### Scenario: Update non-existent sandbox\\n121: \\n122: - **GIVEN** key `session:nonexistent` does not exist\\n123: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\\n124: - **THEN** returns error indicating key does not exist\\n125: \\n126: ---\\n127: \\n128: ## Requirement: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID\\n129: \\n130: The system SHALL delete session key and remove from both ZSETs in one DoMulti batch.\\n131: \\n132: ### Scenario: Delete existing session\\n133: \\n134: - **GIVEN** key `session:todelete` exists and members exist in both ZSETs\\n135: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \\\"todelete\\\")` is called\\n136: - **THEN** executes DoMulti: DEL `session:todelete`, ZREM from `session:expiry`, ZREM from `session:last_activity`\\n137: \\n138: ---\\n139: \\n140: ## Requirement: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes\\n141: \\n142: The system SHALL list sessions with expiry score <= before timestamp using ZRANGEBYSCORE.\\n143: \\n144: ### Scenario: List expired sessions\\n145: \\n146: - **GIVEN** ZSET `session:expiry` contains members with scores\\n147: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 10)` is called with limit > 0\\n148: - **THEN** executes Zrangebyscore with Min(\\\"-inf\\\"), Max(\\\"<before.Unix()>\\\"), Limit(0, 10)\\n149: \\n150: ### Scenario: List expired with limit <= 0\\n151: \\n152: - **GIVEN** any state\\n153: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 0)` is called\\n154: - **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\\n155: \\n156: ---\\n157: \\n158: ## Requirement: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes\\n159: \\n160: The system SHALL list sessions with last-activity score <= before timestamp.\\n161: \\n162: ### Scenario: List inactive sessions\\n163: \\n164: - **GIVEN** ZSET `session:last_activity` contains members with scores\\n165: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 5)` is called with limit > 0\\n166: - **THEN** executes Zrangebyscore on `session:last_activity` with limit\\n167: \\n168: ### Scenario: List inactive with limit <= 0\\n169: \\n170: - **GIVEN** any state\\n171: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 0)` is called\\n172: - **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\\n173: \\n174: ---\\n175: \\n176: ## Requirement: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity\\n177: \\n178: The system SHALL update last-activity timestamp only if session key exists.\\n179: \\n180: ### Scenario: Update activity for existing session\\n181: \\n182: - **GIVEN** key `session:activesession` exists\\n183: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \\\"activesession\\\", someTime)` is called\\n184: - **THEN** verifies key exists via Exists, then ZADD to `session:last_activity`\\n185: \\n186: ### Scenario: Update activity with zero timestamp\\n187: \\n188: - **GIVEN** key `session:activesession` exists\\n189: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \\\"activesession\\\", time.Time{})` is called\\n190: - **THEN** uses `time.Now().Unix()` as the score\\n191: \\n192: ### Scenario: Update activity for non-existent session\\n193: \\n194: - **GIVEN** key `session:missing` does not exist\\n195: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \\\"missing\\\", time.Now())` is called\\n196: - **THEN** returns `ErrNotFound`\\n197: \\n198: ---\\n199: \\n200: ## Requirement: Valkey list loaders tolerate missing keys\\n201: \\n202: The system SHALL use MGET for batch loading and skip keys that return empty/nil.\\n203: \\n204: ### Scenario: Load sandboxes with some missing keys\\n205: \\n206: - **GIVEN** ZSET returns session IDs [\\\"sess1\\\", \\\"sess2\\\", \\\"sess3\\\"]\\n207: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\\n208: - **THEN** executes MGET for all keys, omits any with empty response from result\\n209: \\n210: ---\\n211: \\n212: ## Requirement: Valkey Close\\n213: \\n214: The system SHALL close the Valkey client cleanly.\\n215: \\n216: ### Scenario: Close store\\n217: \\n218: - **GIVEN** an open Valkey store connection\\n219: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\\n220: - **THEN** executes `vs.cli.Close()` and returns nil\\n221: \\n222: ---\\n223: \\n224: ## Requirement: Valkey environment variables\\n225: \\n226: The system SHALL require specific environment variables for Valkey configuration.\\n227: \\n228: ### Scenario: Valkey address required\\n229: \\n230: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\\n231: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\\n232: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating VALKEY_ADDR is required\\n233: \\n234: ### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\\n235: \\n236: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\\n237: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\\n238: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\\n239: \\n240: ### Scenario: Valkey password optional\\n241: \\n242: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\\n243: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\\n244: - **THEN** initialization succeeds with empty password\\n245: \\n246: ---\\n247: \\n248: ## Requirement: ZSET score semantics for Valkey\\n249: \\n250: The system SHALL maintain correct score types for expiry and last-activity ZSETs.\\n251: \\n252: ### Scenario: Expiry score uses sandbox ExpiresAt\\n253: \\n254: - **GIVEN** sandbox with `ExpiresAt` set to specific time\\n255: - **WHEN** sandbox is stored\\n256: - **THEN** ZSET score is `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())`\\n257: \\n258: ### Scenario: Last activity score uses current time on store\\n259: \\n260: - **GIVEN** valid sandbox for storage\\n261: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is executed\\n262: - **THEN** ZSET score is `float64(time.Now().Unix())`\\n263: \\n264: ### Scenario: Last activity score uses provided timestamp on update\\n265: \\n266: - **GIVEN** existing session\\n267: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with specific timestamp\\n268: - **THEN** ZSET score is `float64(at.Unix())`\\n269: \\n270: ---\\n271: \\n272: ## Requirement: Singleton pattern for Valkey store\\n273: \\n274: The system SHALL use sync.Once to ensure single initialization.\\n275: \\n276: ### Scenario: Concurrent Storage() calls\\n277: \\n278: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` simultaneously\\n279: - **WHEN** STORE_TYPE=valkey\\n280: - **THEN** initStore executes exactly once\\n\\n(End of file - total 280 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"# Delta Spec: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\\n\\n## Module\\n`pkg/store`\\n\\n## Language\\nGo\\n\\n## Size\\nS\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Requirement: Valkey provider selection\\n\\nThe system SHALL support Valkey as a store backend when `STORE_TYPE` is set to `valkey` (case-insensitive).\\n\\n### Scenario: Valkey provider selected\\n\\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[]},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775852489668,\"end\":1775852489685}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775852489701,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e874e001XzeYVoxPj5XSB0\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e7b65001LGdvM8uiVZ64Sv\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_f0d8d2985af14082af84df03\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Tasks\\n2: \\n3: **Module:** pkg/store  \\n4: **Language:** Go  \\n5: **Size:** S  \\n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\\n7: \\n8: ---\\n9: \\n10: ## Phase 1: Core Implementation Verification\\n11: \\n12: - [ ] **1.1** Verify `valkeyStore` struct defined in `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` with fields: `cli`, `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`\\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Verify constants are accessible: `sessionKeyPrefix`, `sessionExpiryIndexKey`, `sessionLastActivityKey` (currently shared from `store_redis.go`)\\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Verify `makeValkeyOptions()` parses environment variables: `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE`\\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Verify `VALKEY_ADDR` is required — returns error if empty\\n16: - [ ] **1.5** Verify `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is required when `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not \\\"false\\\"\\n17: - [ ] **1.6** Verify `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles successfully\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## Phase 2: Basic Operations\\n22: \\n23: - [ ] **2.1** Verify `newValkeyStore()` creates client and performs PING check\\n24: - [ ] **2.2** Verify `Ping(ctx)` executes `cli.B().Ping().Build()` and uses `cli.Do(ctx, result)`\\n25: - [ ] **2.3** Verify `Ping` returns error on disconnected server\\n26: - [ ] **2.4** Verify `GetSandboxBySessionID` uses GET command and returns `ErrNotFound` when key not exists\\n27: - [ ] **2.5** Verify `GetSandboxBySessionID` handles `valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error())` correctly\\n28: - [ ] **2.6** Verify `Close()` calls `cli.Close()` and returns any error\\n29: \\n30: ---\\n31: \\n32: ## Phase 3: StoreSandbox Atomicity\\n33: \\n34: - [ ] **3.1** Verify `StoreSandbox` uses `DoMulti` with: SETNX (session key), ZADD (expiry index), ZADD (last_activity index)\\n35: - [ ] **3.2** Verify `StoreSandbox` validates nil sandbox — returns error \\\"sandbox is nil\\\"\\n36: - [ ] **3.3** Verify `StoreSandbox` validates zero ExpiresAt — returns error \\\"invalid expiry: ExpiresAt is zero\\\"\\n37: - [ ] **3.4** Verify `StoreSandbox` validates empty SessionID — returns error \\\"session ID is required\\\"\\n38: - [ ] **3.5** Verify ZSET scores: expiry uses `ExpiresAt.Unix()`, last activity uses `time.Now().Unix()`\\n39: \\n40: ---\\n41: \\n42: ## Phase 4: UpdateSandbox\\n43: \\n44: - [ ] **4.1** Verify `UpdateSandbox` uses SET with XX flag (not SetNX)\\n45: - [ ] **4.2** Verify `UpdateSandbox` fails with error \\\"key not exists\\\" when key does not exist\\n46: - [ ] **4.3** Verify `UpdateSandbox` does NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSETs\\n47: - [ ] **4.4** Verify error handling for `valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error())` case\\n48: \\n49: ---\\n50: \\n51: ## Phase 5: DeleteSandbox\\n52: \\n53: - [ ] **5.1** Verify `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` uses DoMulti with DEL and ZREM (both indices)\\n54: - [ ] **5.2** Verify deletion succeeds for non-existent session (no error returned)\\n55: \\n56: ---\\n57: \\n58: ## Phase 6: List Operations\\n59: \\n60: - [ ] **6.1** Verify `ListExpiredSandboxes` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\\n61: - [ ] **6.2** Verify `ListInactiveSandboxes` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\\n62: - [ ] **6.3** Verify both list operations return `nil, nil` when limit <= 0\\n63: - [ ] **6.4** Verify list operations use MGET to load JSON for each session ID\\n64: - [ ] **6.5** Verify orphan ZSET members are skipped gracefully (check for `item.IsNil()`)\\n65: \\n66: ---\\n67: \\n68: ## Phase 7: UpdateSessionLastActivity\\n69: \\n70: - [ ] **7.1** Verify `UpdateSessionLastActivity` verifies key existence first via EXISTS\\n71: - [ ] **7.2** Verify returns `ErrNotFound` when session key does not exist\\n72: - [ ] **7.3** Verify uses `time.Now()` when timestamp is zero\\n73: - [ ] **7.4** Verify rejects empty session ID with error \\\"session ID is required\\\"\\n74: - [ ] **7.5** Verify ZADD uses provided timestamp as score\\n75: \\n76: ---\\n77: \\n78: ## Phase 8: Unit Tests\\n79: \\n80: - [ ] **8.1** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` — unit tests with mock Valkey\\n81: - [ ] **8.2** Verify `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` passes\\n82: \\n83: ---\\n84: \\n85: ## Dependencies\\n86: \\n87: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\\n88: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\\n89: \\n90: ---\\n91: \\n92: ## References\\n93: \\n94: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md` (if exists)\\n95: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md` (Store interface)\\n96: - Design: `session-store/design.md`\\n97: - Spec: `session-store/spec.md`\\n98: - Redis implementation: `changes/AR-013/tasks.md` (for comparison)\\n\\n(End of file - total 98 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Tasks\\n\\n**Module:** pkg/store  \\n**Language:** Go  \\n**Size:** S  \\n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Phase 1: Core Implementation Verification\\n\\n- [ ] **1.1** Verify `valkeyStore` struct defined in `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` with fields: `cli`, `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`\\n- [ ] **1.2** Verify constants are accessible: `sessionKeyPrefix`, `sessionExpiryIndexKey`, `sessionLastActivityKey` (currently shared from `store_redis.go`)\\n- [ ] **1.3** Verify `makeValkeyOptions()` parses environment variables: `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE`\\n- [ ] **1.4** Verify `VALKEY_ADDR` is required — returns error if empty\\n- [ ] **1.5** Verify `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is required when `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not \\\"false\\\"\\n- [ ] **1.6** Verify `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles successfully\\n\\n---\\n\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[]},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775852489671,\"end\":1775852489698}}}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1775852489731,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e8be4001RLzrV3w5c7cPUa\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e7b65001LGdvM8uiVZ64Sv\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":15545,\"input\":497,\"output\":155,\"reasoning\":0,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":14893}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1775852492793,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e97f7001Jj1oJ7tqOyXVuS\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e8c1b001ChWALEZWvaaIeR\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"snapshot\":\"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775852493906,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e9ad4001sBICR6dYRw0Us1\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e8c1b001ChWALEZWvaaIeR\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"toolu_6f8bfd256b5541af83e442d9\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"**/pkg/store/*valkey*.go\"},\"output\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":1,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775852493892,\"end\":1775852493904}}}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1775852493928,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e9c520014CzwkkJkU2BEL2\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e8c1b001ChWALEZWvaaIeR\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":20082,\"input\":5163,\"output\":66,\"reasoning\":0,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":14853}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1775852496655,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790ea70c001FDxv8U81nyxfu6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e9c87001r11Emb8mvww7A9\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"snapshot\":\"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775852498378,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790ea9d4001lNwYQb9YeB3AjY\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e9c87001r11Emb8mvww7A9\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_ecead446eb754471881c159c\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: package store\\n2: \\n3: import (\\n4: \\t\\\"context\\\"\\n5: \\t\\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n6: \\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n7: \\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n8: \\t\\\"os\\\"\\n9: \\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n10: \\t\\\"time\\\"\\n11: \\n12: \\t\\\"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\\\"\\n13: \\t\\\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\\\"\\n14: \\t\\\"k8s.io/klog/v2\\\"\\n15: )\\n16: \\n17: type valkeyStore struct {\\n18: \\tcli                  valkey.Client\\n19: \\tsessionPrefix        string\\n20: \\texpiryIndexKey       string\\n21: \\tlastActivityIndexKey string\\n22: }\\n23: \\n24: func newValkeyStore() (Store, error) {\\n25: \\topts, err := makeValkeyOptions()\\n26: \\tif err != nil {\\n27: \\t\\treturn nil, err\\n28: \\t}\\n29: \\n30: \\tcli, err := valkey.NewClient(*opts)\\n31: \\tif err != nil {\\n32: \\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to create valkey client: %w\\\", err)\\n33: \\t}\\n34: \\n35: \\tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 5*time.Second)\\n36: \\tdefer cancel()\\n37: \\n38: \\tresult := cli.B().Ping().Build()\\n39: \\tresp := cli.Do(ctx, result)\\n40: \\tpong, err := resp.ToString()\\n41: \\tif err != nil {\\n42: \\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to ping valkey: %w\\\", err)\\n43: \\t}\\n44: \\tif pong != \\\"PONG\\\" {\\n45: \\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"unexpected ping response: %s\\\", pong)\\n46: \\t}\\n47: \\n48: \\treturn &valkeyStore{\\n49: \\t\\tcli:                  cli,\\n50: \\t\\tsessionPrefix:        sessionKeyPrefix,\\n51: \\t\\texpiryIndexKey:       sessionExpiryIndexKey,\\n52: \\t\\tlastActivityIndexKey: sessionLastActivityKey,\\n53: \\t}, nil\\n54: }\\n55: \\n56: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\\n57: \\tvalkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\\\"VALKEY_ADDR\\\")\\n58: \\tif valkeyAddr == \\\"\\\" {\\n59: \\t\\treturn nil, errors.New(\\\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\\\")\\n60: \\t}\\n61: \\n62: \\tvalkeyPasswordRequired := os.Getenv(\\\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\\\")\\n63: \\tvalkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\\\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\\\")\\n64: \\n65: \\tpasswordRequired := true\\n66: \\tif strings.EqualFold(valkeyPasswordRequired, \\\"false\\\") {\\n67: \\t\\tpasswordRequired = false\\n68: \\t}\\n69: \\n70: \\tif passwordRequired && valkeyPassword == \\\"\\\" {\\n71: \\t\\treturn nil, errors.New(\\\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\\\")\\n72: \\t}\\n73: \\n74: \\topts := valkey.ClientOption{\\n75: \\t\\tInitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \\\",\\\"),\\n76: \\t\\tPassword:    valkeyPassword,\\n77: \\t}\\n78: \\n79: \\tif disableCache, _ := os.LookupEnv(\\\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\\\"); strings.EqualFold(disableCache, \\\"true\\\") {\\n80: \\t\\topts.DisableCache = true\\n81: \\t\\tklog.Info(\\\"Valkey DisableCache is enabled\\\")\\n82: \\t}\\n83: \\n84: \\tif forceSingle, _ := os.LookupEnv(\\\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\\\"); strings.EqualFold(forceSingle, \\\"true\\\") {\\n85: \\t\\topts.ForceSingleClient = true\\n86: \\t\\tklog.Info(\\\"Valkey ForceSingleClient is enabled\\\")\\n87: \\t}\\n88: \\n89: \\treturn &opts, nil\\n90: }\\n91: \\n92: func (vs *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\\n93: \\tresult := vs.cli.B().Ping().Build()\\n94: \\tresp := vs.cli.Do(ctx, result)\\n95: \\tpong, err := resp.ToString()\\n96: \\tif err != nil {\\n97: \\t\\treturn err\\n98: \\t}\\n99: \\tif pong != \\\"PONG\\\" {\\n100: \\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"unexpected ping response: %s\\\", pong)\\n101: \\t}\\n102: \\treturn nil\\n103: }\\n104: \\n105: func (vs *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\\n106: \\treturn vs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\\n107: }\\n108: \\n109: func (vs *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\\n110: \\tkey := vs.sessionKey(sessionID)\\n111: \\tresult := vs.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()\\n112: \\tresp := vs.cli.Do(ctx, result)\\n113: \\n114: \\tif valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error()) {\\n115: \\t\\treturn nil, ErrNotFound\\n116: \\t}\\n117: \\tif resp.Error() != nil {\\n118: \\t\\treturn nil, resp.Error()\\n119: \\t}\\n120: \\n121: \\tdata, err := resp.ToString()\\n122: \\tif err != nil {\\n123: \\t\\treturn nil, err\\n124: \\t}\\n125: \\n126: \\tvar sandbox types.SandboxInfo\\n127: \\tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\\n128: \\t\\treturn nil, err\\n129: \\t}\\n130: \\n131: \\treturn &sandbox, nil\\n132: }\\n133: \\n134: func (vs *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error {\\n135: \\tif sandboxStore == nil {\\n136: \\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"sandbox is nil\\\")\\n137: \\t}\\n138: \\tif sandboxStore.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\\n139: \\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"invalid expiry: ExpiresAt is zero\\\")\\n140: \\t}\\n141: \\tif sandboxStore.SessionID == \\\"\\\" {\\n142: \\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"session ID is required\\\")\\n143: \\t}\\n144: \\n145: \\tkey := vs.sessionKey(sandboxStore.SessionID)\\n146: \\tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandboxStore)\\n147: \\tif err != nil {\\n148: \\t\\treturn err\\n149: \\t}\\n150: \\n151: \\tnow := time.Now().Unix()\\n152: \\texpiryScore := float64(sandboxStore.ExpiresAt.Unix())\\n153: \\tlastActivityScore := float64(now)\\n154: \\n155: \\tcmds := []valkey.Completed{\\n156: \\t\\tvs.cli.B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build(),\\n157: \\t\\tvs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).ZaddScoreMember(valkey.ZaddScoreMember{Score: expiryScore, Member: sandboxStore.SessionID}).Build(),\\n158: \\t\\tvs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).ZaddScoreMember(valkey.ZaddScoreMember{Score: lastActivityScore, Member: sandboxStore.SessionID}).Build(),\\n159: \\t}\\n160: \\tresults := vs.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)\\n161: \\tfor _, r := range results {\\n162: \\t\\tif err := r.Error(); err != nil {\\n163: \\t\\t\\treturn err\\n164: \\t\\t}\\n165: \\t}\\n166: \\n167: \\treturn nil\\n168: }\\n169: \\n170: func (vs *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error {\\n171: \\tif sandboxStore == nil {\\n172: \\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"sandbox is nil\\\")\\n173: \\t}\\n174: \\tif sandboxStore.SessionID == \\\"\\\" {\\n175: \\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"session ID is required\\\")\\n176: \\t}\\n177: \\n178: \\tkey := vs.sessionKey(sandboxStore.SessionID)\\n179: \\tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandboxStore)\\n180: \\tif err != nil {\\n181: \\t\\treturn err\\n182: \\t}\\n183: \\n184: \\tresult := vs.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()\\n185: \\tresp := vs.cli.Do(ctx, result)\\n186: \\n187: \\tif valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error()) {\\n188: \\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"key not exists\\\")\\n189: \\t}\\n190: \\tif resp.Error() != nil {\\n191: \\t\\treturn resp.Error()\\n192: \\t}\\n193: \\n194: \\tok, err := resp.ToString()\\n195: \\tif err != nil {\\n196: \\t\\treturn err\\n197: \\t}\\n198: \\tif ok != \\\"OK\\\" {\\n199: \\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"key not exists\\\")\\n200: \\t}\\n201: \\n202: \\treturn nil\\n203: }\\n204: \\n205: func (vs *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\\n206: \\tkey := vs.sessionKey(sessionID)\\n207: \\n208: \\tcmds := []valkey.Completed{\\n209: \\t\\tvs.cli.B().Del().Key(key).Build(),\\n210: \\t\\tvs.cli.B().Zrem().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\\n211: \\t\\tvs.cli.B().Zrem().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\\n212: \\t}\\n213: \\tresults := vs.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)\\n214: \\tfor _, r := range results {\\n215: \\t\\tif err := r.Error(); err != nil {\\n216: \\t\\t\\treturn err\\n217: \\t\\t}\\n218: \\t}\\n219: \\n220: \\treturn nil\\n221: }\\n222: \\n223: func (vs *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\\n224: \\tif limit <= 0 {\\n225: \\t\\treturn nil, nil\\n226: \\t}\\n227: \\n228: \\tresult := vs.cli.B().\\n229: \\t\\tZrangebyscore().\\n230: \\t\\tKey(vs.expiryIndexKey).\\n231: \\t\\tMin(\\\"-inf\\\").\\n232: \\t\\tMax(fmt.Sprintf(\\\"%d\\\", before.Unix())).\\n233: \\t\\tLimit(0, limit).\\n234: \\t\\tBuild()\\n235: \\tresp := vs.cli.Do(ctx, result)\\n236: \\tif resp.Error() != nil {\\n237: \\t\\treturn nil, resp.Error()\\n238: \\t}\\n239: \\n240: \\tsessionIDs, err := resp.AsStrSlice()\\n241: \\tif err != nil {\\n242: \\t\\treturn nil, err\\n243: \\t}\\n244: \\n245: \\treturn vs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\\n246: }\\n247: \\n248: func (vs *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\\n249: \\tif limit <= 0 {\\n250: \\t\\treturn nil, nil\\n251: \\t}\\n252: \\n253: \\tresult := vs.cli.B().\\n254: \\t\\tZrangebyscore().\\n255: \\t\\tKey(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).\\n256: \\t\\tMin(\\\"-inf\\\").\\n257: \\t\\tMax(fmt.Sprintf(\\\"%d\\\", before.Unix())).\\n258: \\t\\tLimit(0, limit).\\n259: \\t\\tBuild()\\n260: \\tresp := vs.cli.Do(ctx, result)\\n261: \\tif resp.Error() != nil {\\n262: \\t\\treturn nil, resp.Error()\\n263: \\t}\\n264: \\n265: \\tsessionIDs, err := resp.AsStrSlice()\\n266: \\tif err != nil {\\n267: \\t\\treturn nil, err\\n268: \\t}\\n269: \\n270: \\treturn vs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\\n271: }\\n272: \\n273: func (vs *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\\n274: \\tif len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\\n275: \\t\\treturn nil, nil\\n276: \\t}\\n277: \\n278: \\tkeys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\\n279: \\tfor i, sid := range sessionIDs {\\n280: \\t\\tkeys[i] = vs.sessionKey(sid)\\n281: \\t}\\n282: \\n283: \\tresult := vs.cli.B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build()\\n284: \\tresp := vs.cli.Do(ctx, result)\\n285: \\tif resp.Error() != nil {\\n286: \\t\\treturn nil, resp.Error()\\n287: \\t}\\n288: \\n289: \\tsliceResp, err := resp.ToArray()\\n290: \\tif err != nil {\\n291: \\t\\treturn nil, err\\n292: \\t}\\n293: \\n294: \\tvar sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\\n295: \\tfor i, item := range sliceResp {\\n296: \\t\\tif item.IsNil() {\\n297: \\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n298: \\t\\t}\\n299: \\n300: \\t\\tstr, err := item.ToString()\\n301: \\t\\tif err != nil || str == \\\"\\\" {\\n302: \\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n303: \\t\\t}\\n304: \\n305: \\t\\tvar sandbox types.SandboxInfo\\n306: \\t\\tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(str), &sandbox); err != nil {\\n307: \\t\\t\\tklog.V(4).Infof(\\\"failed to unmarshal sandbox %s: %v\\\", sessionIDs[i], err)\\n308: \\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n309: \\t\\t}\\n310: \\t\\tsandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\\n311: \\t}\\n312: \\n313: \\treturn sandboxes, nil\\n314: }\\n315: \\n316: func (vs *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\\n317: \\tif sessionID == \\\"\\\" {\\n318: \\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"session ID is required\\\")\\n319: \\t}\\n320: \\n321: \\tkey := vs.sessionKey(sessionID)\\n322: \\texistsResult := vs.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build()\\n323: \\texistsResp := vs.cli.Do(ctx, existsResult)\\n324: \\tif existsResp.Error() != nil {\\n325: \\t\\treturn existsResp.Error()\\n326: \\t}\\n327: \\texists, _ := existsResp.AsInt64()\\n328: \\tif exists != 1 {\\n329: \\t\\treturn ErrNotFound\\n330: \\t}\\n331: \\n332: \\ttimestamp := at\\n333: \\tif timestamp.IsZero() {\\n334: \\t\\ttimestamp = time.Now()\\n335: \\t}\\n336: \\n337: \\tscore := float64(timestamp.Unix())\\n338: \\tupdateResult := vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).Score(score).Member(sessionID).Build()\\n339: \\tupdateResp := vs.cli.Do(ctx, updateResult)\\n340: \\tif updateResp.Error() != nil {\\n341: \\t\\treturn updateResp.Error()\\n342: \\t}\\n343: \\n344: \\treturn nil\\n345: }\\n346: \\n347: func (vs *valkeyStore) Close() error {\\n348: \\treturn vs.cli.Close()\\n349: }\\n\\n(End of file - total 349 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"package store\\n\\nimport (\\n\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n\\t\\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n\\n\\t\\\"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\\\"\\n\\t\\\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\\\"\\n\\t\\\"k8s.io/klog/v2\\\"\\n)\\n\\ntype valkeyStore struct {\\n\\tcli                  valkey.Client\\n\\tsessionPrefix        string\\n\\texpiryIndexKey       string\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[]},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.