rt_d790e82d9001yC19Vtk15ARmX2\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e7b65001LGdvM8uiVZ64Sv\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_b07a9015917946c1950fd64e\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\\n2: \\n3: ## Module\\n4: `pkg/store`\\n5: \\n6: ## Language\\n7: Go\\n8: \\n9: ## Size\\n10: S\\n11: \\n12: ---\\n13: \\n14: ## Requirement: Valkey provider selection\\n15: \\n16: The system SHALL support Valkey as a store backend when `STORE_TYPE` is set to `valkey` (case-insensitive).\\n17: \\n18: ### Scenario: Valkey provider selected\\n19: \\n20: - **GIVEN** environment variable `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\\n21: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is first called\\n22: - **THEN** the Valkey implementation is initialized\\n23: \\n24: ---\\n25: \\n26: ## Requirement: Valkey client initialization\\n27: \\n28: The system SHALL create a Valkey client using `valkey-go` library with address and password from environment variables.\\n29: \\n30: ### Scenario: Valkey client created with multiple addresses\\n31: \\n32: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=valkey-node-1:6379,valkey-node-2:6379` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD=secret`\\n33: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\\n34: - **THEN** client is created with `InitAddress: [\\\"valkey-node-1:6379\\\", \\\"valkey-node-2:6379\\\"]` and `Password: \\\"secret\\\"`\\n35: \\n36: ### Scenario: Valkey client with cache disabled\\n37: \\n38: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` and valid `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\\n39: - **WHEN** Valkey options are built\\n40: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is set to `true` on the client options\\n41: \\n42: ### Scenario: Valkey client with single client mode\\n43: \\n44: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true` and valid `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\\n45: - **WHEN** Valkey options are built\\n46: - **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is set to `true` on the client options\\n47: \\n48: ---\\n49: \\n50: ## Requirement: Valkey Ping operation\\n51: \\n52: The system SHALL verify Valkey connectivity by sending PING command and expecting \\\"PONG\\\" response.\\n53: \\n54: ### Scenario: Ping successful\\n55: \\n56: - **GIVEN** a running Valkey server\\n57: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Valkey store\\n58: - **THEN** command `B().Ping()` returns string \\\"PONG\\\"\\n59: \\n60: ### Scenario: Ping fails on disconnected server\\n61: \\n62: - **GIVEN** Valkey server is unavailable\\n63: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\\n64: - **THEN** error is returned indicating connection failure\\n65: \\n66: ---\\n67: \\n68: ## Requirement: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID\\n69: \\n70: The system SHALL retrieve sandbox JSON by session key using GET command.\\n71: \\n72: ### Scenario: Session found\\n73: \\n74: - **GIVEN** key `session:test-session` exists with valid JSON in Valkey\\n75: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \\\"test-session\\\")` is called\\n76: - **THEN** returns `*types.SandboxInfo` with data unmarshaled from JSON\\n77: \\n78: ### Scenario: Session not found\\n79: \\n80: - **GIVEN** key `session:missing-session` does not exist in Valkey\\n81: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \\\"missing-session\\\")` is called\\n82: - **THEN** returns `ErrNotFound` (detected via `IsValkeyNil`)\\n83: \\n84: ---\\n85: \\n86: ## Requirement: Valkey StoreSandbox\\n87: \\n88: The system SHALL store sandbox JSON using SETNX and update both ZSET indexes in one DoMulti batch.\\n89: \\n90: ### Scenario: Store new sandbox\\n91: \\n92: - **GIVEN** a valid `*types.SandboxInfo` with `SessionID=newsession` and `ExpiresAt` set\\n93: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\\n94: - **THEN** executes DoMulti with: SETNX `session:newsession`, ZADD to `session:expiry`, ZADD to `session:last_activity`\\n95: \\n96: ### Scenario: Store sandbox with zero ExpiresAt\\n97: \\n98: - **GIVEN** `*types.SandboxInfo` with `ExpiresAt` set to zero time\\n99: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\\n100: - **THEN** error indicates invalid expiration time\\n101: \\n102: ### Scenario: Store nil sandbox\\n103: \\n104: - **GIVEN** nil sandbox pointer\\n105: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\\n106: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\\n107: \\n108: ---\\n109: \\n110: ## Requirement: Valkey UpdateSandbox\\n111: \\n112: The system SHALL update existing sandbox JSON using SET with XX flag.\\n113: \\n114: ### Scenario: Update existing sandbox\\n115: \\n116: - **GIVEN** key `session:existing` exists with valid JSON\\n117: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, updatedSandbox)` is called\\n118: - **THEN** executes SET with XX flag, expects response `ToString() == \\\"OK\\\"`\\n119: \\n120: ### Scenario: Update non-existent sandbox\\n121: \\n122: - **GIVEN** key `session:nonexistent` does not exist\\n123: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\\n124: - **THEN** returns error indicating key does not exist\\n125: \\n126: ---\\n127: \\n128: ## Requirement: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID\\n129: \\n130: The system SHALL delete session key and remove from both ZSETs in one DoMulti batch.\\n131: \\n132: ### Scenario: Delete existing session\\n133: \\n134: - **GIVEN** key `session:todelete` exists and members exist in both ZSETs\\n135: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \\\"todelete\\\")` is called\\n136: - **THEN** executes DoMulti: DEL `session:todelete`, ZREM from `session:expiry`, ZREM from `session:last_activity`\\n137: \\n138: ---\\n139: \\n140: ## Requirement: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes\\n141: \\n142: The system SHALL list sessions with expiry score <= before timestamp using ZRANGEBYSCORE.\\n143: \\n144: ### Scenario: List expired sessions\\n145: \\n146: - **GIVEN** ZSET `session:expiry` contains members with scores\\n147: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 10)` is called with limit > 0\\n148: - **THEN** executes Zrangebyscore with Min(\\\"-inf\\\"), Max(\\\"<before.Unix()>\\\"), Limit(0, 10)\\n149: \\n150: ### Scenario: List expired with limit <= 0\\n151: \\n152: - **GIVEN** any state\\n153: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 0)` is called\\n154: - **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\\n155: \\n156: ---\\n157: \\n158: ## Requirement: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes\\n159: \\n160: The system SHALL list sessions with last-activity score <= before timestamp.\\n161: \\n162: ### Scenario: List inactive sessions\\n163: \\n164: - **GIVEN** ZSET `session:last_activity` contains members with scores\\n165: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 5)` is called with limit > 0\\n166: - **THEN** executes Zrangebyscore on `session:last_activity` with limit\\n167: \\n168: ### Scenario: List inactive with limit <= 0\\n169: \\n170: - **GIVEN** any state\\n171: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 0)` is called\\n172: - **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\\n173: \\n174: ---\\n175: \\n176: ## Requirement: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity\\n177: \\n178: The system SHALL update last-activity timestamp only if session key exists.\\n179: \\n180: ### Scenario: Update activity for existing session\\n181: \\n182: - **GIVEN** key `session:activesession` exists\\n183: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \\\"activesession\\\", someTime)` is called\\n184: - **THEN** verifies key exists via Exists, then ZADD to `session:last_activity`\\n185: \\n186: ### Scenario: Update activity with zero timestamp\\n187: \\n188: - **GIVEN** key `session:activesession` exists\\n189: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \\\"activesession\\\", time.Time{})` is called\\n190: - **THEN** uses `time.Now().Unix()` as the score\\n191: \\n192: ### Scenario: Update activity for non-existent session\\n193: \\n194: - **GIVEN** key `session:missing` does not exist\\n195: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \\\"missing\\\", time.Now())` is called\\n196: - **THEN** returns `ErrNotFound`\\n197: \\n198: ---\\n199: \\n200: ## Requirement: Valkey list loaders tolerate missing keys\\n201: \\n202: The system SHALL use MGET for batch loading and skip keys that return empty/nil.\\n203: \\n204: ### Scenario: Load sandboxes with some missing keys\\n205: \\n206: - **GIVEN** ZSET returns session IDs [\\\"sess1\\\", \\\"sess2\\\", \\\"sess3\\\"]\\n207: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\\n208: - **THEN** executes MGET for all keys, omits any with empty response from result\\n209: \\n210: ---\\n211: \\n212: ## Requirement: Valkey Close\\n213: \\n214: The system SHALL close the Valkey client cleanly.\\n215: \\n216: ### Scenario: Close store\\n217: \\n218: - **GIVEN** an open Valkey store connection\\n219: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\\n220: - **THEN** executes `vs.cli.Close()` and returns nil\\n221: \\n222: ---\\n223: \\n224: ## Requirement: Valkey environment variables\\n225: \\n226: The system SHALL require specific environment variables for Valkey configuration.\\n227: \\n228: ### Scenario: Valkey address required\\n229: \\n230: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\\n231: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\\n232: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating VALKEY_ADDR is required\\n233: \\n234: ### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\\n235: \\n236: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\\n237: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\\n238: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\\n239: \\n240: ### Scenario: Valkey password optional\\n241: \\n242: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\\n243: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\\n244: - **THEN** initialization succeeds with empty password\\n245: \\n246: ---\\n247: \\n248: ## Requirement: ZSET score semantics for Valkey\\n249: \\n250: The system SHALL maintain correct score types for expiry and last-activity ZSETs.\\n251: \\n252: ### Scenario: Expiry score uses sandbox ExpiresAt\\n253: \\n254: - **GIVEN** sandbox with `ExpiresAt` set to specific time\\n255: - **WHEN** sandbox is stored\\n256: - **THEN** ZSET score is `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())`\\n257: \\n258: ### Scenario: Last activity score uses current time on store\\n259: \\n260: - **GIVEN** valid sandbox for storage\\n261: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is executed\\n262: - **THEN** ZSET score is `float64(time.Now().Unix())`\\n263: \\n264: ### Scenario: Last activity score uses provided timestamp on update\\n265: \\n266: - **GIVEN** existing session\\n267: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with specific timestamp\\n268: - **THEN** ZSET score is `float64(at.Unix())`\\n269: \\n270: ---\\n271: \\n272: ## Requirement: Singleton pattern for Valkey store\\n273: \\n274: The system SHALL use sync.Once to ensure single initialization.\\n275: \\n276: ### Scenario: Concurrent Storage() calls\\n277: \\n278: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` simultaneously\\n279: - **WHEN** STORE_TYPE=valkey\\n280: - **THEN** initStore executes exactly once\\n\\n(End of file - total 280 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"# Delta Spec: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\\n\\n## Module\\n`pkg/store`\\n\\n## Language\\nGo\\n\\n## Size\\nS\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Requirement: Valkey provider selection\\n\\nThe system SHALL support Valkey as a store backend when `STORE_TYPE` is set to `valkey` (case-insensitive).\\n\\n### Scenario: Valkey provider selected\\n\\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[]},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775852489668,\"end\":1775852489685}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775852489701,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e874e001XzeYVoxPj5XSB0\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e7b65001LGdvM8uiVZ64Sv\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_f0d8d2985af14082af84df03\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Tasks\\n2: \\n3: **Module:** pkg/store  \\n4: **Language:** Go  \\n5: **Size:** S  \\n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\\n7: \\n8: ---\\n9: \\n10: ## Phase 1: Core Implementation Verification\\n11: \\n12: - [ ] **1.1** Verify `valkeyStore` struct defined in `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` with fields: `cli`, `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`\\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Verify constants are accessible: `sessionKeyPrefix`, `sessionExpiryIndexKey`, `sessionLastActivityKey` (currently shared from `store_redis.go`)\\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Verify `makeValkeyOptions()` parses environment variables: `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE`\\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Verify `VALKEY_ADDR` is required — returns error if empty\\n16: - [ ] **1.5** Verify `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is required when `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not \\\"false\\\"\\n17: - [ ] **1.6** Verify `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles successfully\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## Phase 2: Basic Operations\\n22: \\n23: - [ ] **2.1** Verify `newValkeyStore()` creates client and performs PING check\\n24: - [ ] **2.2** Verify `Ping(ctx)` executes `cli.B().Ping().Build()` and uses `cli.Do(ctx, result)`\\n25: - [ ] **2.3** Verify `Ping` returns error on disconnected server\\n26: - [ ] **2.4** Verify `GetSandboxBySessionID` uses GET command and returns `ErrNotFound` when key not exists\\n27: - [ ] **2.5** Verify `GetSandboxBySessionID` handles `valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error())` correctly\\n28: - [ ] **2.6** Verify `Close()` calls `cli.Close()` and returns any error\\n29: \\n30: ---\\n31: \\n32: ## Phase 3: StoreSandbox Atomicity\\n33: \\n34: - [ ] **3.1** Verify `StoreSandbox` uses `DoMulti` with: SETNX (session key), ZADD (expiry index), ZADD (last_activity index)\\n35: - [ ] **3.2** Verify `StoreSandbox` validates nil sandbox — returns error \\\"sandbox is nil\\\"\\n36: - [ ] **3.3** Verify `StoreSandbox` validates zero ExpiresAt — returns error \\\"invalid expiry: ExpiresAt is zero\\\"\\n37: - [ ] **3.4** Verify `StoreSandbox` validates empty SessionID — returns error \\\"session ID is required\\\"\\n38: - [ ] **3.5** Verify ZSET scores: expiry uses `ExpiresAt.Unix()`, last activity uses `time.Now().Unix()`\\n39: \\n40: ---\\n41: \\n42: ## Phase 4: UpdateSandbox\\n43: \\n44: - [ ] **4.1** Verify `UpdateSandbox` uses SET with XX flag (not SetNX)\\n45: - [ ] **4.2** Verify `UpdateSandbox` fails with error \\\"key not exists\\\" when key does not exist\\n46: - [ ] **4.3** Verify `UpdateSandbox` does NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSETs\\n47: - [ ] **4.4** Verify error handling for `valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error())` case\\n48: \\n49: ---\\n50: \\n51: ## Phase 5: DeleteSandbox\\n52: \\n53: - [ ] **5.1** Verify `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` uses DoMulti with DEL and ZREM (both indices)\\n54: - [ ] **5.2** Verify deletion succeeds for non-existent session (no error returned)\\n55: \\n56: ---\\n57: \\n58: ## Phase 6: List Operations\\n59: \\n60: - [ ] **6.1** Verify `ListExpiredSandboxes` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\\n61: - [ ] **6.2** Verify `ListInactiveSandboxes` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\\n62: - [ ] **6.3** Verify both list operations return `nil, nil` when limit <= 0\\n63: - [ ] **6.4** Verify list operations use MGET to load JSON for each session ID\\n64: - [ ] **6.5** Verify orphan ZSET members are skipped gracefully (check for `item.IsNil()`)\\n65: \\n66: ---\\n67: \\n68: ## Phase 7: UpdateSessionLastActivity\\n69: \\n70: - [ ] **7.1** Verify `UpdateSessionLastActivity` verifies key existence first via EXISTS\\n71: - [ ] **7.2** Verify returns `ErrNotFound` when session key does not exist\\n72: - [ ] **7.3** Verify uses `time.Now()` when timestamp is zero\\n73: - [ ] **7.4** Verify rejects empty session ID with error \\\"session ID is required\\\"\\n74: - [ ] **7.5** Verify ZADD uses provided timestamp as score\\n75: \\n76: ---\\n77: \\n78: ## Phase 8: Unit Tests\\n79: \\n80: - [ ] **8.1** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` — unit tests with mock Valkey\\n81: - [ ] **8.2** Verify `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` passes\\n82: \\n83: ---\\n84: \\n85: ## Dependencies\\n86: \\n87: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\\n88: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\\n89: \\n90: ---\\n91: \\n92: ## References\\n93: \\n94: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md` (if exists)\\n95: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md` (Store interface)\\n96: - Design: `session-store/design.md`\\n97: - Spec: `session-store/spec.md`\\n98: - Redis implementation: `changes/AR-013/tasks.md` (for comparison)\\n\\n(End of file - total 98 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Tasks\\n\\n**Module:** pkg/store  \\n**Language:** Go  \\n**Size:** S  \\n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Phase 1: Core Implementation Verification\\n\\n- [ ] **1.1** Verify `valkeyStore` struct defined in `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` with fields: `cli`, `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`\\n- [ ] **1.2** Verify constants are accessible: `sessionKeyPrefix`, `sessionExpiryIndexKey`, `sessionLastActivityKey` (currently shared from `store_redis.go`)\\n- [ ] **1.3** Verify `makeValkeyOptions()` parses environment variables: `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE`\\n- [ ] **1.4** Verify `VALKEY_ADDR` is required — returns error if empty\\n- [ ] **1.5** Verify `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is required when `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not \\\"false\\\"\\n- [ ] **1.6** Verify `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles successfully\\n\\n---\\n\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[]},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775852489671,\"end\":1775852489698}}}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1775852489731,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e8be4001RLzrV3w5c7cPUa\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e7b65001LGdvM8uiVZ64Sv\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":15545,\"input\":497,\"output\":155,\"reasoning\":0,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":14893}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1775852492793,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e97f7001Jj1oJ7tqOyXVuS\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e8c1b001ChWALEZWvaaIeR\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"snapshot\":\"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775852493906,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d790e9ad4001sBICR6dYRw0Us1\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d790e8c1b001ChWALEZWvaaIeR\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286f19899ffedhs66tN0pElNQ7\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"toolu_6f8bfd256b5541af83e442d9\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"**/pkg/store/*valkey*.go\"},\"output\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":1,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_202604